      {
        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "**H⁺ (the proton)** tops the list with **4,081 different ligands** — more than double the runner-up, Cu²⁺. This makes sense because protonation equilibria (pKₐ values) are measured for virtually every acid-base-active ligand, making H⁺ the most universally studied \"metal\" in the database.",
